Happy Saturday ❤️

node.text:
NEW WAYS TO PAINT WITH KIDS 🎨• New and Unique Art Experiences for your Toddlers, Preschoolers and Big kids! ••••••••••• Tap that bookmark and save this list of ideas at the end for when you need them. I’ve scrolled waaaaaayyyy back in my feed for you and there are 25 awesome ways to paint that my kids and I have loved. My personal faves are painting with sponges and pom poms 🤗 No surprise there! 😉 Painting can be a beneficial experience for our children for so many reasons! Give them the chance to get messy, creative, and experience new materials 👉👉 Which ones will you try at home? Make sure to tag friends who might benefit from this list as well 👇🥰 
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
🐛 CATERPILLAR COLORS 🌈• Fill the colorful circles of the caterpillar! This color matching and fine motor activity has an easy setup - trace around a cup or bowl in each color to create your caterpillar. Provide dot markers or stickers for your toddler to dot and match colors. Save this one to try later! Leave a comment, tag a friend and let me know if you’ll try this at home 🥰👇Happy Tuesday!

.
.
.
.

node.text:
🍎 APPLE STAMP TREES 🌳🍂 One of our favorite ways to paint is with half an apple as a stamp! Apple stamping is a classic art project for preschoolers and this is a fun way to take it a bit further and use the stamps to make a seasonal fall tree as autumn approaches! 🤗🍂🌳 Inspo: @crafty_morning blog ••••••• Setup: Cut an apple in half and set out with paints. Draw a tree with branches on a large roll of paper. Encourage dipping + stamping the apples to make a tree full of autumn colors or simply make a green tree 🌳 if you have plenty of summer left ahead! 👉👉 Will you try this one at home?! Tag a friend who might love this fall project as well👇🥰 and don’t forget to bookmark the post for September! 
.
.

node.text: ALPHABET LEARNING LOCKS 🔐 @lakeshorelearning #ad | These lock and key resources are so intriguing for little ones! If you’ve been here a while, then you know I love sharing playful home learning resources from Lakeshore and these have a been a big hit in our house! •••• These learning locks help kids recognize uppercase and lowercase letters and explore letter sounds. Encourage your little one to simply choose a key and match it to the letter or to the picture on the lock. When they make a match, the key will turn and the lock will open! NAME WORK for preschoolers 🎨 🤩👉 Encourage your little one to practice writing/ forming the letters in their name! Swipe over to see each one in action. ••••• Set up a large piece of paper or cardboard with their name written + different tools for your little one to use. ❤️👉 We used some of my favorite art supplies and ways to paint for this activity with my almost 4 yo! Finger paint, dot along the lines, and Q-tip trace over the letters in your name! ••••• Little ones will love the challenge of forming the letters in different ways! ❤️👌 Save this one for later with the bookmark below and share with a friend who might like it as well 🥰👇

CUPCAKE MONSTER CRAFT| Easy invitation to create cupcake liner monsters! 🌈👻• Toddlers and preschoolers everywhere will love this simple, open-ended project 🤗 You’ll need: some kind of cupcake liners! Any colors and designs will be great.👌I love that the liners give the monsters that fuzzy look 🤩👀 Googley eyes are a good addition but eyes can be drawn on or made from paper cutouts as well. Markers, pom poms, and any other supplies are up to you! Watch as your child gets creative adding lots of eyes, arms, legs, hair etc. •••••••• Bookmark 🔖 below to save this project for the week ahead & don’t forget to take your momma friends in comments below 👇❤️

node.text:
🎨SPONGE PAINTING 🖼 5 EASY CRAFTS for kids 🌈🤩👉 Painting with sponge stamps is one of our absolute favorite ways to create! It’s a great alternative to the usual paintbrush and a soft kitchen sponge (I get ours at Dollar Tree) can be easily cut into almost any shape to use for stamping! ••••• Make one of these 5 adorable ideas with your kiddos at home with just a sponge and some washable paints. •••••• Share with a momma friend you’d love an art/ play date with ❤️👇and leave comment with which one you will try! Make sure to bookmark this post to save these fun ideas 💡 for later ❤️🌈
